The paper discusses a new family of codes and a decoding scheme that approaches the capacity of the AWGN channel. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses message-passing formulation on a factor graph, which is a common technique in Network Information Theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the connection between the LDLC decoder and belief propagation, which is a popular technique in Statistical Inference (cs.SI). The paper proposes an efficient construction of sparse generator matrix and its matching decoder, which is a common technique in Distributed Systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses experimental results, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
